social_posts.post_text: Want to hear some good news? Jesus bore the weight of our sin and shame at the cross. Therefore, our slate can be clean when we ask for His forgiveness. Don't allow the enemy to win the war in your mind. Jesus can take on any shame you feel and replace it with His righteousness.
If you're looking for direction, Jesus is the Source of hope to run to. He is THE way, THE truth, and THE life.

We were never promised a life free from sorrow, but we were promised joy in spite of the sorrow. "For his anger lasts only a moment, but his favor lasts a lifetime! Weeping may last through the night, but joy comes with the morning." - Psalm 30:5
One of the best ways to show God our appreciation for His faithfulness is through our obedience.

Wait on the Lord. He will renew your strength! 🙌🏼 “But those who hope in the Lord will renew their strength. They will soar on wings like eagles; they will run and not grow weary, they will walk and not be faint.” Isaiah 40:31
Your fears show you lies. Time to turn the tables. God is bigger than your greatest fear. 🙏
"He heals the brokenhearted and bandages their wounds." - Psalm 147:3 If you're experiencing a broken heart today, look to God. He can heal you.
Want to do something great in God's Kingdom? Surrender your will, and obey His. God isn't looking for perfect people. He's looking for those who will say "yes" and submit to Him.

"Instead, he gave up his divine privileges; he took the humble position of a slave and was born as a human being." - Philippians 2:7 Jesus modeled servanthood for us. Let's make that our motivation today.

This might seem like a season of waiting, but God is here with you. "Even when I walk through the darkest valley, I will not be afraid, for you are close beside me. Your rod and your staff protect and comfort me." - Psalm 23:4
God is in control, it is in His hands. Pray about it, and give it to God!
You are one praise away from your greatest miracle!
God is the solution for everything we go through in life, even loneliness. Draw close to Him, and watch Him comfort you, today and always.

Set your sights on Jesus. His peace will flood your soul. "Be anxious for nothing, but in everything, by prayer and petition, with thanksgiving, present your requests to God. And the peace of God, which surpasses all understanding, will guard your hearts and your minds in Christ Jesus." - Philippians 4:6-7
Jesus Christ is the same yesterday and today, and forever.
If you are currently in a waiting season, be encouraged that God's timing is perfect and more beautiful than we could ever dream up. Tag someone who needs this reminder today.
Prayer not only changes our circumstances but has the power to change us too.

"For we are God’s masterpiece. He has created us anew in Christ Jesus, so we can do the good things he planned for us long ago." - Ephesians 2:10 "'For I know the plans I have for you,' declares the LORD, 'plans to prosper you and not to harm you, plans to give you hope and a future.'" - Jeremiah 29:11
This is why it's so important to feed ourselves the Word of God. We can either become like the latest Netflix binge, or we can become what God's Word says we are.

One of the greatest lies of the Devil is that you are alone; that nobody would truly love you if they knew the real you. But that’s just it...it’s a lie meant to isolate you. Don’t believe it! Feeling weak? Feeling isolated? Get into community. It’s not just hanging out; it’s life exchange. It’s strength.

We aren’t promised that we won’t be tempted. But when we are, God will provide us with a way out. He won’t let us become trapped. It isn’t our strength that saves us from the temptation, but God’s.
Fear not; Fear is false evidence appearing real.

"And God will generously provide all you need. Then you will always have everything you need and plenty left over to share with others." Blessing doesn't always mean money. It means a storehouse of life that we can give out to others.
"He heals the brokenhearted and bandages their wounds." - Psalm 147:3. If you're experiencing a broken heart today, look to God. He can heal you.
Want to live a life that honors God? Pursue holiness. The more we seek God, the more we get to know who He is and live a life that is pleasing to Him.

There is power in prayer. Don't ever forget that. It's not just a ritual before a meal. It's not just a way we open service. It's power. Our prayers have power because the One who hears them is all-powerful.
God, we believe that greater things lie ahead. Greater things are still in store for those who trust You.
Psalms 86:9-10, "All the nations you have made will come and worship before you, Lord; they will bring glory to your name. For you are great and do marvelous deeds; you alone are God."

For the spirit of the Lord would say unto thee, His children, "Fret not the thief that comes by night nor the arrow by day. For I, the Lord thy God, am causing a season of recompense to come nigh thy dwelling. For many days now, the enemy has tried thee and said that surely you will fall, but you did not!" saith the Lord. I have seen you stand even in the lowest of valleys and proclaim My Name regardless of what was thrown at you. I am pleased in thee and will speak now to the Accuser of the Saints that enough is enough! No more will he test you in this manner!

This year, I am bringing a season of recompense and reconciliation to my body. The things that you have lacked, you will lack no more. The healings needed in your body, I will give. In this season, saith God, I will pour out my Spirit amongst you, and you will prophesy like those of old. You will say that the Lord has not forsaken me and remembered me! Get ready; revival draws near!

Now go, saith the Lord. For tonight I will send my ministering angels to your dwelling to bring peace. I declare that today and henceforth this year, you will know that I am the Lord, your God!

-Prophet Tracy Cooke

We may face many challenges and uncertainties in life, but we can find peace and guidance through the Holy Spirit. When we invite Him into our lives, He leads us with His wisdom and grace, showing us the way to go and comforting us in our struggles. Let's open our hearts to the Holy Spirit and trust in His guidance to help us navigate the complexities of life. He is our source of strength, our counselor, and our helper. Let's lean on Him and allow Him to work in us and through us for His glory.

Life can be unpredictable and chaotic, but we can find stability and security in God. He is our rock and refuge, a safe haven in the midst of the storm. When we feel overwhelmed and uncertain, let's turn to Him and rest in His peace. He promises to provide for our needs and to guide us through every trial and challenge we face. Let's trust in His faithfulness and His unfailing love, knowing that He is always with us, no matter what. In Him, we can find strength, hope, and a firm foundation for our lives.

Sometimes in life, we may feel uncertain about the future and what it holds. However, we can find comfort in the fact that God has a plan for our lives, and His plans are always good. Even when we cannot see the way forward, we can trust in His timing and His ways. Let's have faith that He will guide us through every season of life and that His plans will ultimately lead us to a place of joy, peace, and fulfillment. As we surrender our lives to Him, let's trust that He will work all things together for our good and His glory.

God's love is the greatest force in the universe, and it is available to all of us, no matter who we are or what we have done. As we experience His love, let's extend it to others and love one another as He has loved us. Let's be a shining light in the world, showing kindness, compassion, and forgiveness to those around us. Let's strive to build bridges instead of walls, and to seek unity instead of division. When we love one another with God's love, we can make a difference in our communities and in the world. Let's choose to love unconditionally and without limits, just as God has loved us.

Life can be full of trials and temptations that can make us feel weak and vulnerable. But God's grace is always sufficient for us, and it gives us the strength and wisdom we need to overcome every obstacle. Let's draw near to Him and receive His grace, knowing that He will never leave us or forsake us. When we seek His wisdom and guidance, He will lead us through every challenge we face, and we can emerge stronger and more resilient on the other side. Let's rely on His grace to sustain us, and let's trust in His unfailing love for us.

As Christians, we have been blessed with spiritual gifts from the Holy Spirit. These gifts are not meant for our own benefit, but rather for the common good and the building up of the body of Christ. Let's use our gifts to serve others and to spread God's love and truth to the world around us. Whether it's through teaching, serving, encouraging, or any other gift, let's use them to bring glory to God and to make a difference in the lives of others. When we use our gifts in this way, we are fulfilling our purpose as members of the body of Christ, and we are contributing to the growth and flourishing of the church. Let's be faithful stewards of the gifts we have been given and use them to make a positive impact in the world.

In a world that constantly bombards us with messages about who we should be and what we should value, it's easy to lose sight of our true identity. Heavenly Father,
We come before You with gratitude and humility, acknowledging Your sovereign presence in our lives. Thank You for the gift of another day, for the breath in our lungs, and for the countless blessings that surround us.
In moments of joy, we praise You, recognizing that every good and perfect gift comes from above. Your love fills our hearts, and we are grateful for the abundant grace that sustains us through each season of life.
Lord, in times of trial and tribulation, we seek Your strength and guidance. Grant us the wisdom to navigate challenges and the faith to trust in Your divine plan. Help us overcome any obstacles that stand in our way, knowing that You are with us, guiding us through the darkest valleys.
We lift up those who are hurting, suffering, or in need. May Your comforting presence be felt by those facing illness, grief, or despair. Bring healing to the brokenhearted, and may Your peace that surpasses all understanding envelop them.
Father, we pray for our world, beseeching You to bring about reconciliation, understanding, and unity. Heal the divisions that separate us and guide us in the paths of justice, mercy, and compassion. May Your light shine brightly in the darkest corners, dispelling hatred and fostering love.
As we navigate the journey of life, we surrender my plans and desires to You. Your ways are higher, and Your thoughts are greater than ours. Lead us in the direction You have ordained for us, and grant us the courage to follow Your will with unwavering faith.
We thank You for the relationships that enrich our lives, for family and friends who support and uplift us. Bless those around us, and may our interactions be filled with kindness, understanding, and love.
In Jesus' name, we pray. Amen. 🙏✨
